THE wet weather didn't dampen the spirits of Gaga's Little Monsters despite many camping overnight outside Glasgow's SSE Hydro in a bid to catch a glimpse of their idol. Lady Gaga in Glasgow: Little Monsters brave the rain as they eagerly await superstar's arrival - Daily Record 
A RAINBOW shone into the SSE Hydro as fans awaited Lady Gaga's arrival for her gig tonight.
The wet weather didn't dampen her Little Monsters spirits despite many of camping overnight outside the venue.
Amongst them were dressed up fans Megan, Nick&nbsp; and Lindsay who claimed they loved Gaga's 'creative expression,&nbsp; fashion and love for her fans.&quot;
Lindsay offered to cook her done food and Megan added: &quot;We will love you like your mother.&quot;


 